<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 6:06AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A WINTRY MIX WILL AFFECT
APPOMATTOX...NORTHWESTERN CHARLOTTE...SOUTH CENTRAL ROCKBRIDGE...
CAMPBELL...NORTHERN HENRY...SOUTHWESTERN BUCKINGHAM...EAST CENTRAL
BOTETOURT...PITTSYLVANIA...NORTHWESTERN HALIFAX...BEDFORD...SOUTHERN
AMHERST AND FRANKLIN COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF LYNCHBURG...
At 601 AM EST, a band of rain changing to snow was located near
Ajax, or near Penhook, moving northeast at 35 mph.
Wind gusts 30 to 50 mph are possible within this band of
precipitation. Watch for large tree limbs and potential power
outages.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Bedford...
Rocky Mount...
Altavista...
Amherst...
Appomattox...
and Hurt.
Please monitor local media outlets and the national weather service
for further statements.
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time when traveling.</description>
